text.tspan: openTECR is an open-source effort by passionation bioinformaticians across
the world. Intersted researchers are encouraged to join our google group
(hyperlink) where updates and efforts are shared and organized across the
The "Contribute" page (hyperlink) provides a means for researchers
to submit their curated data -- either in our format or another format -- and
suggestions for literature that we should curate into openTECR.
Overhead for the project is jointly supported by KBase (a Science-Focus Area
of the Department of Energy) and the National Institute of Standards and
Technology (a subsidiary of the Department of Commerce) of the USA.
